HIV/AIDS: Sin ta samu karuwar kashi 14 cikin 100 na sababbin cututtuka
Kasar Sin ta sanar da karuwar kashi 14 cikin 100 na yawan mutanen da ke dauke da cutar HIV da AIDS.
Fiye da mutane 820,000 ne suka sha wahala a kasar, in ji hukumar kiwon lafiya.
An samu sabbin shari'o'i kimanin 40,000 a cikin kwata na biyu na shekarar 2018.
Yawancin sababbin lokuta sun kasance ta hanyar jima'i, kuma sun nuna canji daga baya.
A al'ada, HIV ya yada cikin sauri a wasu sassan kasar Sin sakamakon kamuwa da cutar ta jini.
Amma yawan mutanen da suka kamu da cutar HIV ta wannan hanyar, an rage zuwa kusan sifili, wani jami'in kiwon lafiya na kasar Sin ya ce a wani taro a lardin Yunnan.
Amma daga shekara zuwa shekara, yawan mutanen da ke fama da cutar HIV da AIDS a kasar Sin ya karu da mutane 100,000.
Yada HIV ta hanyar jima'i babbar matsala ce a cikin al'ummar LGBT na kasar Sin.
An yi watsi da jima'i a kasar Sin a shekarar 1997, amma ana zargin cewa ana nuna bambanci ga mutane na LGBT/HBTQ.
Saboda dabi'un da ake bi a kasar, bincike ya nuna cewa kashi 70-90 cikin dari na maza da ke yin jima'i da maza, a karshe za su auri mata.
